perform the SIMLR clustering algorithm

SIMLR(
  X,
  c,
  no.dim = NA,
  k = 10,
  if.impute = FALSE,
  normalize = FALSE,
  cores.ratio = 1
)

Arguments

X

an (m x n) data matrix of gene expression measurements of individual cells or and object of class SCESet

c

number of clusters to be estimated over X

no.dim

number of dimensions

k

tuning parameter

if.impute

should I traspose the input data?

normalize

should I normalize the input data?

cores.ratio

ratio of the number of cores to be used when computing the multi-kernel

Value

clusters the cells based on SIMLR and their similarities list of 8 elements describing the clusters obtained by SIMLR, of which y are the resulting clusters: y = results of k-means clusterings, S = similarities computed by SIMLR, F = results from network diffiusion, ydata = data referring the the results by k-means, alphaK = clustering coefficients, execution.time = execution time of the present run, converge = iterative convergence values by T-SNE, LF = parameters of the clustering
